[[Religion]] and [[agriculture]] have been closely associated since [[neolithic]] times and the development of early [[Orphism (religion)|Orphic]] religions based upon [[fertility]] and the [[season]]s.<ref name=Falvey>{{citation|url=http://www.iid.org/publications/Religion_Agriculture.pdf|author=Lindsay Falvey|year=2005|title=Religion and Agriculture: Sustainability in Christianity and Buddhism|publisher=Institute for International Development|format=PDF|pages=13–14|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080706135745/http://www.iid.org/publications/Religion_Agriculture.pdf|archivedate=2008-07-06|df=}}</ref>
